## Authoritative Sources (curated)

A user-maintained list of trusted external sources. `meta-researcher` MUST consult these sources first before general internet research to improve signal-to-noise ratio. `pe-meta-release-monitor` uses this list to supplement its standard fetch targets.

| # | Source | URL | Type | Last checked | Trust level |
|---|---|---|---|---|---|
| 1 | VS Code Copilot Customization docs | `https://code.visualstudio.com/docs/copilot/copilot-customization` | Official docs | 2026-04-27 | High |
| 2 | GitHub Copilot Extensions docs | `https://docs.github.com/en/copilot` | Official docs | — | High |
| 3 | Anthropic Prompt Engineering Guide | `https://docs.anthropic.com/en/docs/build-with-claude/prompt-engineering/overview` | Vendor docs | — | High |
| 4 | OpenAI Prompt Engineering Guide | `https://platform.openai.com/docs/guides/prompt-engineering` | Vendor docs | — | High |
| 5 | VS Code Release Notes | `https://code.visualstudio.com/updates` | Official docs | 2026-04-27 | High |
| 6 | GitHub Copilot Changelog | `https://github.blog/changelog/label/copilot/` | Official docs | 2026-04-27 | High |
| 7 | MCP Specification | `https://modelcontextprotocol.io/specification` | Spec | — | High |

**Maintenance**: Add or remove sources as needed. Update "Last checked" after each `meta-researcher` or `release-monitor` run that consulted the source.

