## Override History

Tracks cases where the user overrides a CRITICAL or UNSAFE finding during Phase 5 approval in the meta-update pipeline. Each override is logged here so the next scheduled review can check whether overridden findings have manifested as real problems.

| Date | Finding | Severity | User decision | Rationale (if provided) | Follow-up due | Follow-up result |
|---|---|---|---|---|---|---|
| — | _No overrides recorded yet_ | — | — | — | — | — |

**How to use**:
- **pe-meta-update** appends a row here whenever the user approves a change rated UNSAFE or overrides a CRITICAL finding during Phase 5
- **pe-meta-scheduled-review** checks this table in Phase 1.3 for entries with blank "Follow-up result" and evaluates whether the overridden issue has manifested
- After follow-up, update the "Follow-up result" column with the outcome

